A colony of ants has 500 members. Each ant collects 2 grains of sand per minute.

If the ants work for 3 hours, how many grains of sand will they collect in total?

Remember, there are 60 minutes in an hour. Show your work. $$
\begin{aligned}
\text{grains per ant per hour} &= 2 \frac{\text{grains}}{\text{minute}} \cdot 60 \frac{\text{minutes}}{\text{hour}} = 120 \frac{\text{grains}}{\text{hour}} \\
\text{grains per colony per hour} &= 120 \frac{\text{grains}}{\text{hour}} \cdot 500 \text{ants} = 60000 \frac{\text{grains}}{\text{hour}} \\
\text{total grains} &= 60000 \frac{\text{grains}}{\text{hour}} \cdot 3 \text{hours} = 180000 \text{grains}
\end{aligned}
$$

