A group of 5 friends decides to walk for 30 minutes each day to improve their health. They aim to walk a total of 15 miles per week. If they walk at an average speed of 3 miles per hour, how many days will it take them to reach their goal?

Remember to show your calculations. $$
\begin{aligned}
\text{Daily distance} &= \frac{3 \text{ miles}}{\text{hour}} \times \frac{1}{2} \text{ hour} = 1.5 \text{ miles}\\
\text{Days to reach goal} &= \frac{15 \text{ miles}}{1.5 \text{ miles/day}} = 10 \text{ days}
\end{aligned}
$$

A train travels at 80 miles per hour. If it leaves New York City at 9:00 AM and travels to Boston, a distance of 220 miles, what time will it arrive in Boston? $$
\text{Time} = \frac{\text{Distance}}{\text{Speed}} = \frac{220 \text{ miles}}{80 \text{ miles per hour}} = 2.75 \text{ hours}
$$

$$
2.75 \text{ hours} \times 60 \text{ minutes per hour} = 165 \text{ minutes}
$$

$$
9:00 \text{ AM} + 165 \text{ minutes} = 12:45 \text{ PM} 
$$

